Hello!
In order to try to save results in resultdb mongodb collection without serialisation of json i try to override ResultDB class in my test project, like this:
```python
from pyspider.database.mongodb.resultdb import *

class MyResultDB(ResultDB):
    def save(self, project, taskid, url, result):
        collection_name = self._collection_name(project)
        obj = {
            'taskid': taskid,
            'url': url,
            'result': result,
            'json_result': result,
            'updatetime': time.time(),
        }
        return self.database[collection_name].update(
            {'taskid': taskid}, {"$set": self._stringify(obj)}, upsert=True
        )
```
But it seems not doing anything in resultdb - there still only 5 fields - "_id",  "taskid", "url", "updatetime" and serialised "result".
Pretty newbie in python, need help =)

