My particular arrangement was thus:

```
class CustomQuerySet(PolymorphicQuerySet):
    def some_method(self):
        return


class AbstractPolymorphicModel(PolymorphicModel):
    objects = PolymorphicManager(CustomQuerySet)
    class Meta:
        abstract = True


class RealPolymorphicModel(AbstractPolymorphicModel):
    pass
```
`RealPolymorphicModel.objects.some_method()` did not exist, and I had to add `objects = PolymorphicManager(CustomQuerySet)` to `RealPolymorphicModel`
